# code-quality-enforcement-gates — History

## v1.3.0 (2026-06-26) — Add §12: sync deprecation docs with a DeprecationWarning symbol (PLANNING-stage)

**Changed by:** /learn session — ProjectHephaestus issue #1508 deprecation-doc-sync plan (PLANNING stage)
**Verification:** verified-local for the pre-existing §1–§11 content; the NEW §12 sub-pattern is `unverified` (planning-stage; the plan was written but the markdown annotations and the property-based regression test were NOT implemented or CI-run — no markdownlint, no pytest this session)

### What changed

Added **§12 — Sync Deprecation Docs with a DeprecationWarning Symbol** (planning-stage sub-pattern of §3 deprecation-gate + §5 assert-property), covering the doc-vs-runtime deprecation-sync gap: a function emits `DeprecationWarning` in code but COMPATIBILITY.md / `docs/MIGRATION.md` don't reflect it.

- **Mirror the precedent, don't invent conventions.** Find the ONE symbol already correctly annotated (here `retry_with_jitter`) and mirror BOTH mechanisms: inline `(deprecated)` table annotation AND a prose callout; copy removal-timeline wording verbatim for deprecation-policy consistency (POLA).
- **Guard the INVARIANT with a property-based test, not literal text.** Assert `emits DeprecationWarning ⇒ annotated in COMPATIBILITY.md AND listed in MIGRATION.md Deprecated-symbols section` — §5 applied to docs.
- **Make the test fully OFFLINE.** Read committed `.md` files + trigger the warning via the imported function with `pytest.warns(DeprecationWarning)`; no `gh`/network/auth ⇒ no silent-false-green-on-unauth risk (the §11 failure mode).
- Recorded durable risks: brittle MIGRATION.md section-scoping (split-on-next-H2/H3 silently mis-scopes if a sibling H3 is inserted or the heading text changes); stale line/coordinate refs (`COMPATIBILITY.md:210/190-195/214/238-243`, `MIGRATION.md:59-66`, `utils.py:329-335`) — re-grep at edit time; markdownlint (MD013/MD055/MD056) NOT verified on the long inline row + em-dash callout; warning-trigger ordering assumption (holds because `warn()` is first body statement at `utils.py:329`, breaks if a refactor moves it past an early return); unverified `#deprecation-policy` anchor-slug reuse.

Added: 1 description Use-when item (10) + 11 tags, 1 When-to-Use trigger (#13), 1 Quick Reference row, 9 Failed Attempts rows, 1 Verified On row (ProjectHephaestus #1508, planning/unverified). Version 1.2.0 → 1.3.0; date → 2026-06-26.

### Why

A planning session for ProjectHephaestus #1508 surfaced a transferable pattern: when code-level deprecation outpaces the human-facing migration/compatibility docs, the durable lessons are (a) mirror the existing precedent symbol's annotation rather than inventing wording, and (b) guard the doc-vs-runtime invariant with a property-based OFFLINE test so there is no network/auth dependency and no silent-false-green. Captured honestly as planning-stage/unverified because the annotations and test were not implemented or CI-run.

