## v1.2.0 (2026-06-20) — Add §11: verify a tracking/remediation doc's checkboxes before editing

**Changed by:** /learn session — ProjectProteus remediation-plan checkbox correction (PLANNING stage)
**Verification:** verified-local for the pre-existing §1–§10 content; the NEW §11 sub-pattern is `unverified` (planning-stage; the property regression test was not implemented or CI-run)

### What changed

Extended Detailed Step 10 (verify findings vs ground truth) with a new planning-stage sub-pattern as **§11 — Verify a Tracking/Remediation Doc's Checkboxes Before Editing**:

- When the task is "fix stale `- [ ]`/`- [x]` state in a remediation/roadmap/status doc," the doc's own claims AND the triggering bug report's stale-list are NOT authoritative — verify EVERY box against live `gh issue view <n> --json state`. In the originating session this surfaced two extra stale entries (#92, #100) the issue body never named.
- Checkbox semantics nuance: Wave-3 lines are PR-GROUP scoped — `box ticked ⟺ ALL issue numbers on the line CLOSED`; do not tick a group with an open child (#98/#101/#103).
- Guard re-drift with a PROPERTY-based regression test (`all referenced issues CLOSED ⇒ ticked`, fires only on all-closed lines), wired into the existing CI test job — applying §5 to a doc.
- Recorded risks: silent false-green from `gh`-skip-on-unauth; network/rate-limit dependency; point-in-time snapshot reopen risk; stale line/coordinate refs (line 21/25, `_required.yml:158-159` `dispatch-contract-test`) — re-grep at edit time.
- Cross-pointer to the dedicated `tracking-doc-checkbox-sync-regression-guard` skill (verified-local committed-fixture invariant table) which supersedes the live-`gh` guard design.

Added: 1 When-to-Use trigger (#12), 1 Quick Reference row, 4 Failed Attempts rows (trusted issue body's stale-list; treated PR-group lines as per-issue; literal-text regression test; gh-skip-on-unauth false-green), 1 Verified On row (ProjectProteus, planning/unverified), and 3 description tags. Description Use-when item (9) added. Version 1.1.0 → 1.2.0; date → 2026-06-20.

### Why

A planning session to correct a stale remediation-tracking doc proved that neither the doc nor the issue that requested the fix can be trusted as the source of checkbox truth — per-box live verification is mandatory, and a property-based guard (not a literal-text or silently-skipping live guard) is needed to stop re-drift. This is a concrete, durable extension of §10's ground-truth principle, kept honest as planning-stage/unverified.

