## Superseded from ci-deprecation-enforcement

```yaml
name: ci-deprecation-enforcement
description: Promote a CI grep warning into a hard exit-1 enforcement gate for deprecated symbols
category: ci-cd
date: 2026-02-20
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
```

Promote a CI `::warning::` grep step to `::error::` + `exit 1` enforcement gate.
Issue #786, PR #834.

Key findings:
- Count MUST be 0 before switching to exit 1.
- Two distinct grep-v patterns needed: `grep -v "# deprecated"` (standalone comment lines) AND
  `grep -v "(deprecated)"` (inline docstring annotations) — neither alone is sufficient.
- Re-export `__init__.py` files need their own `grep -v` exclusion path.
- Diagnostic grep block inside the `if` must mirror all new exclusions.
- Step name must change from "Track..." to "Enforce..." to signal intent.
- Only `.github/workflows/test.yml` changes required — no Python source changes.

Failed attempts: None — direct approach worked when count was confirmed 0 first.

