```yaml
name: ruff-c901-mccabe-complexity
description: "Skill: ruff-c901-mccabe-complexity"
category: tooling
date: 2026-03-19
version: "1.0.0"
user-invocable: false
```

Enable C901 McCabe complexity rule in ruff with a pragmatic threshold. Issue #1377 (follow-up
from #1356). 65 violations at threshold 10; 0 violations after threshold 12 + annotated noqa.

Threshold decision: Accept complexity 11–12 (22 functions) for orchestration/CLI code;
suppress complexity >12 (43 functions) with rationale via `# noqa: C901`.

Critical: noqa comment MUST be on the `def` line, not on the return-type line. Ruff silently
ignores noqa on any line other than the `def` line for multi-line function signatures.

pyproject.toml config:
```toml
[tool.ruff.lint]
select = ["E", "F", "W", "I", "N", "D", "UP", "S101", "B", "SIM", "C4", "C901", "RUF"]

[tool.ruff.lint.mccabe]
max-complexity = 12
```

Results: 4434 tests passed, 1 skipped; 75.23% coverage; 29 source files with noqa suppressions.

